    errdefer result.deinit();

    for (legacy.iterator()) |*entry| {
        const score = entry.key;
        const letters = entry.value;
        for (letters) |c| {
            const lower = std.ascii.toLower(c);
            try result.put(lower, score);
        }
    }

    return result;
}
```

Check: std.ascii.toLower takes u8 and returns u8. Good.

Need to ensure we import std.ascii? Actually std.ascii is available via std.

Thus final answer.

